cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CY, cs.SI, cs.IR 

The paper focuses on machine learning approaches for utilizing big data generated by smart cities. Specifically, it discusses the use of deep reinforcement learning and semi-supervised learning for improving smart city services. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CY (Computers and Society) as the paper also discusses the societal impact of smart cities. Additionally, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) are also possible categories as the paper discusses the challenges and opportunities of utilizing big data in smart cities.
